article.headline: Miami 72, Temple 66
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Darius Rice scored 25 points to lead Miami to a 72-66 victory against Temple on Saturday in the Orange Bowl Classic. Rice made a season-high five 3-pointers and added five rebounds and three assists. His final assist led to Gary Hamilton's layup that helped seal the game with about a minute to play. Hamilton's bucket made it 68-64, then Eric Wilkins got a steal and hit a free throw to push the lead to five with 44 seconds remaining. The Hurricanes (6-3) scored 10 of the final 12 points in the game after the Owls (3-5) led 64-62 with less than two minutes to play. Miami has won four of its last five games. This victory was a complete turnaround from Miami's previous game against Florida State. The Hurricanes led 58-54 before missing their final seven shots and losing 67-58 last Sunday. Temple led 22-14 late in the first half before Rice sparked a 13-4 run for Miami. He hit two 3-pointers to held the Hurricanes cut the lead to 30-29 at the break. Rice finished 5-of-9 from beyond the arc and 9-of-16 from the floor. Robert Hite added 15 points, and Guillermo Diaz chipped in 10 off the bench. Diaz scored twice on acrobatic up-and-under moves, plus on an alley-oop. David Hawkins led the Owls with 28 points on 8-of-20 shooting and had seven rebounds. But he went 1-of-6 from the 3-point line, adding to Temple's woes from long range. The Owls finished 5-of-23 from beyond the arc. Temple was relegated to long-range jumpers after losing 7-foot-1 center Keith Butler to a face injury midway through the first half. Butler, who entered the game averaging 8.3 points and 6.8 rebounds, did not return. The Hurricanes played a second consecutive game without forward Will Frisby. The team is waiting to see if he committed an undisclosed NCAA infraction.
